{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5e006d75-8bcc-4764-a862-4e7090a327a6","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` can't verify *which line* threw — any `ArgumentNullException` in the test passes, masking bugs.\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, inner exception, etc.).\n- If using **xUnit**, it's `Assert.Throws<T>`; **NUnit** uses `Assert.Throws<T>` as well.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"47fede7d-0a49-4f43-bcaf-8f93efc1f895","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no tool calls needed.","outputTokens":279,"requestId":"042F:135AB6:19380B4:1C99925:69E820FF"},"id":"f67c2853-ae96-4515-be70-c8d336ab4c55","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:14:46.253Z","parentId":"085e9a83-8762-4718-a897-54bc3decfd6e"}
